<br>
It's a human tragedy every time it happens. And I can't understand how it happens. I don't have kids yet, but probably will in the next 3-5 years. I have two kittens though. And even it's 5am when I hear a crash in the livingroom I am four big steps away from the bed by the time I am awake. I care alot about my kittens.<br>
<br>
I have a very hard time believing I will be slower to catch up on what a kid is doing. Porsche makes cars that are slower from 0-100mphs than me if I hear a sibling do something involving crashing noises in another room.<br>
<br>
And leaving toddlers unsupervised anywhere but in their crib or equal areas? I don't think so. <br>
<br>
